Interface ReferenceCounting

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DAGNode, DataTrainable, Layer, LineSearchCursor, OrientationStrategy<T>, SampledTrainable, StochasticComponent, TensorList, Trainable, TrainableDataMask
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayTrainable, BasicTrainable, BatchedTrainable, CachedTrainable, ConstantResult, ConstL12Normalizer, CountingResult, DAGNetwork, Delta, DeltaSet, DescribeOrientationWrapper, DoubleBuffer, DoubleBufferSet, DoubleBufferSet.Delegate, FailsafeLineSearchCursor, GradientDescent, InnerNode, IterativeTrainer, L12Normalizer, LayerBase, LBFGS, LineSearchCursorBase, LineSearchPoint, LoggingWrapperLayer, MomentumStrategy, MonitoringWrapperLayer, MutableResult, OrientationStrategyBase, OwlQn, PipelineNetwork, PlaceholderLayer, PointSample, QuantifyOrientationWrapper, ReferenceCountingBase, RegisteredObjectBase, ReshapedTensorList, Result, SampledArrayTrainable, SampledCachedTrainable, SimpleLineSearchCursor, SimpleLossNetwork, State, StateSet, SupervisedNetwork, Tensor, TensorArray, TensorListTrainable, TrainableBase, TrainableWrapper, ValidatingOrientationWrapper, ValueLayer, WrapperLayer

    public interface ReferenceCounting
    Interface for objects apply reference counting. Reference counted objects will be freed when the last reference is freed, in a guaranteed-once-only manner. In general, valid reference counting behavior can be maintained by observing a few rules: 1) References should be freed as soon as they are finished being used 2) Only reference counting objects should be used to hold pointers to other reference counting objects, and those pointers should be freed and clears when the object is freed. 3) If returning a reference to an object from a method, increment its reference count. 4) Handle reference counted objects within the scope of a single method when possible. (i.e. prefer to keep them on the stack, not heap.)
